TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Computer-Based Corporate Planning System
AU  - Hamilton, William F.
AU  - Moses, Michael A.
Y1  - 1974/10/01
PY  - 1974
DA  - 1974/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.21.2.148
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.21.2.148
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 148
EP  - 159
VL  - 21
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The key to effective analytical support of the strategic planning process is not simply a corporate model, but an integrated system of models with appropriate software support. This paper describes a computer-based corporate planning system which combines the analytical power of optimization with simulation capabilities and more specialized planning models as elements of an interactive management system. The system has been designed to aid both periodic and ad hoc planning decisions in a large multi-national firm and can be implemented in a wide variety of corporate contexts.
