TY  - JOUR
T1  - Coefficient of Network Complexity
AU  - Kaimann, Richard A.
Y1  - 1974/10/01
PY  - 1974
DA  - 1974/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.21.2.172
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.21.2.172
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 172
EP  - 177
VL  - 21
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The degree of complexity of a critical path network may be classified by calculating a Coefficient of Network Complexity. It is defined as the quotient of activities squared divided by events or preceding work items squared divided by work items. Three distinct contributions are offered. First, the CNC may serve as an indicator of the attention spent in planning the project. Second, the CNC may be used to derive a predictor of network computer processing time. Third, the CNC value suggests the appropriate processing scheme.
